The aim of the course is to give a general and introductory overview of the Greek Christian literature and of its most important texts of the first eight centuries, during which textual pericopes in original language will be examined.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to give a general and introductory overview of the Greek Christian literature of the first eight centuries. The course takes under examination the most important patristic authors, their works and philosophical and theological understandings (incl. biblical hermeneutics and exegesis).

The practical part of the course gives an overview of the tools - catalogues, sources and databases - that are necessary for patristic research.
Also, during the course, different pericopes of patristic texts, that are translated to Estonian or English, will be examined.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student who has passed the course: 1. Is familiar with the main authors of the Greek patristic literature of the first eight centuries and knows their works, literary genres, hermeneutics and historical and cultural contexts. 2. Uses the necessary tools - catalogues, sources and databases -  in order to conduct a patristic research.
